Subject: RE: [VB] Door Resto

I used a heavy rubber-on-aluminum roof seam sealer that 
comes in rolls 8" wide or so from the Home Despot. Peel 
and stick, then brush on the Henry's roofing patch 
everywhere else. The doors go 'thunk' like a Mercedes. 

 -Harry in Fresno
> I used brown pare bag, made templates to fit into every hole I could stuff
> something in, and cut out pieces of 3/8" blue Styrofoam and glued in place
> with H-2 contact cement. It deadens the rattles of the tin and adds a little
> insulation. Plus, it's completely waterproof.
